.TH GORMTOOL 1 "@DATE@" "Gorm @VERSION@" "GNUstep User Commands"
.SH NAME
gormtool \- headless utility for GNUstep Gorm documents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gormtool
.RI [ options ] " inputfile"
.br
.B gormtool
.B --read
.I inputfile
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
gormtool is a command-line front end for selected Gorm document operations.
It runs as a headless AppKit process, opens a Gorm document, performs one or
more operations, optionally writes the modified document, and exits.
.PP
The tool is intended for automation and batch workflows such as localization
import/export, class metadata import/export, and archive conversion.
.SH INPUT SELECTION
.TP
.B --read \fIpath\fR
Use \fIpath\fR as the input document.
.TP
.I inputfile
If \fB--read\fR is omitted, the last command-line argument is treated as the
input file.
.PP
If no valid input document is resolved, the tool exits with an error.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Document I/O
.TP
.B --read \fIpath\fR
Open the input archive from \fIpath\fR.
.TP
.B --write \fIpath\fR
Write the processed archive to \fIpath\fR. The output type is inferred from
the file extension.
.TP
.B --output-path \fIdirectory\fR
Directory used when exporting class source files with \fB--export-class\fR.
Default is the current directory.
.SS Strings and XLIFF
.TP
.B --export-strings-file \fIpath\fR
Export localizable strings from the document to a .strings file.
.TP
.B --import-strings-file \fIpath\fR
Import translated strings from a .strings file into the in-memory document.
.TP
.B --export-xliff \fIpath\fR
Export localizable strings to an XLIFF 1.2 file.
.TP
.B --import-xliff \fIpath\fR
Import translations from an XLIFF 1.2 file into the in-memory document.
.TP
.B --source-language \fIcode\fR
Source language used during XLIFF export.
.TP
.B --target-language \fIcode\fR
Optional target language used during XLIFF export.
.SS Class Import and Export
.TP
.B --import-class \fIheader\fR
Parse an Objective-C header and import class metadata into the document.
.TP
.B --export-class \fIname\fR
Export class \fIname\fR to generated source files.
.SS Inspection and Reporting
.TP
.B --connections
Print connection objects from the document.
.TP
.B --classes
Print custom class metadata.
.TP
.B --objects
Print top-level objects.
.TP
.B --errors
Print the current file preferences profile.
.TP
.B --warnings
Print the current file preferences profile.
.TP
.B --notices
Print the current file preferences profile.
.SS Interactive Mode
.TP
.B --test
Enter test mode after processing options and keep the process running until
interrupted.
.SH NOTES
Operations that modify document state in memory (for example, string or XLIFF
imports) are not persisted unless \fB--write\fR is also provided.
.PP
Although option flags can appear in any order, processing follows the internal
execution order of gormtool.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I *.gorm
Gorm interface documents.
.TP
.I *.nib
Legacy interface archives accepted by Gorm document handling.
.TP
.I *.xib
XML interface archives accepted by Gorm document handling.
.SH EXAMPLES
Export strings from a document:
.PP
.RS
.B gormtool --export-strings-file Localizable.strings MyWindow.gorm
.RE
.PP
Import translated strings and save to a new file:
.PP
.RS
.B gormtool --read MyWindow.gorm --import-strings-file fr.strings --write MyWindow-fr.gorm
.RE
.PP
Export XLIFF with explicit source and target languages:
.PP
.RS
.B gormtool MyWindow.gorm --source-language en --target-language fr --export-xliff MyWindow.xliff
.RE
.PP
Import XLIFF and persist changes:
.PP
.RS
.B gormtool --read MyWindow.gorm --import-xliff MyWindow-fr.xliff --write MyWindow-fr.gorm
.RE
.PP
Convert archive format:
.PP
.RS
.B gormtool --read MyWindow.gorm --write MyWindow.xib
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
gormtool returns 0 on success and non-zero on failure.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at https://github.com/gnustep/apps-gorm/issues or by email to
bug-gnustep@gnu.org.
.SH AUTHORS
Gorm is maintained by the GNUstep community.
.SH SEE ALSO
gorm(1), openapp(1)
